eiteam.esteemedinnovation.api.exosuit

Interface ExosuitUpgrade

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExosuitEventHandler

    public interface ExosuitUpgrade
extends ExosuitEventHandler
    The interface which allows an item to be upgraded into an Exosuit armor piece.

    You must inherit Item, or provide a new implementation for isInstalled, as the default implementation checks if we are an instance of Item.

        default com.google.common.collect.Multimap<java.lang.String,net.minecraft.entity.ai.attributes.AttributeModifier> getAttributeModifiersForExosuit(net.minecraft.inventory.EntityEquipmentSlot armorSlot,
                                                                                                                                                  net.minecraft.item.ItemStack armorPieceStack)
        Called to add attribute modifiers from the upgrade (or plate) to the exosuit armor piece.
        Parameters:
        armorSlot - The slot that the armor is in
        armorPieceStack - The ItemStack holding the armor piece
        Returns:
        A Multimap that will have all of its entries added to the armor's attribute modifiers. Default implementation returns an empty multimap.
